I've searched long for the DVD version of Hamlet by Kenneth Branagh.
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamlet_(1996_film)&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hamlet_(1996_film)&lt;/a&gt;

Finally I found it on eMule.

It was a double DVD edition with English and Italian audio.
Unfortunately for me the only subtitles available in it were in Italian.

But I needed also the original English subtitles: once in my life I wanted to watch the movie with the original dub and with the precise dialogues in english written below.

You know - I can babble in English, but I would be lost to listen to Shakespeare's speech with no aid. So I said: Do it yourself.

I found the english subtitles on Internet.
I demuxed the two DVDs (which were also deprived of their menus) and rebuilt them adding menus and the english subs. A sore task, believe me... but the result was worth the effort.

There you have it:

PAL

For the main movie:
English, Italian audio
English, Italian subs


For the extras:
English audio, Italian subs

There are two ISO, each one fitting a single layer DVD and I added separately the two subtitles files in SRT text format (if there is someone so crazy amongst you who want to try to add his own subtitles: you can use the provided ones to synchronize yours).

The whole task was performed with free software available in Internet (VobEdit, DVD Lab Pro 2) and a small program of mine to shift the time offsets in SRT files for resynch.

If somebody is interested to learn how to demux and rebuild a DVD, drop me a note and I will provide you help.

The 2 DVDs work like a charm on my cheap DVD player on TV... So, enjoy :)


